title: Le locataire
overview: A bureaucrat rents a Paris apartment where he finds himself drawn into a rabbit hole of dangerous paranoia.

title: Roma
overview: A year in the life of a middle-class family's maid in Mexico City in the early 1970s.
stars: ['Yalitza Aparicio', 'Marina de Tavira', 'Diego Cortina Autrey', 'Carlos Peralta']

title: Detachment
overview: A substitute teacher who drifts from classroom to classroom finds a connection to the students and teachers during his latest assignment.

title: Wonder
overview: Based on the New York Times bestseller, this movie tells the incredibly inspiring and heartwarming story of August Pullman, a boy with facial differences who enters the fifth grade, attending a mainstream elementary school for the first time.

title: Fight Club
overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

title: Ladri di biciclette
overview: In post-war Italy, a working-class man's bicycle is stolen. He and his son set out to find it.

title: Ordinary People
overview: The accidental death of the older son of an affluent family deeply strains the relationships among the bitter mother, the good-natured father, and the guilt-ridden younger son.

title: Lifeboat
overview: Several survivors of a torpedoed merchant ship in World War II find themselves in the same lifeboat with one of the crew members of the U-boat that sank their ship.

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: Central do Brasil
overview: An emotive journey of a former school teacher, who writes letters for illiterate people, and a young boy, whose mother has just died, as they search for the father he never knew.

title: Boyhood
overview: The life of Mason, from early childhood to his arrival at college.

title: Forushande
overview: While both participating in a production of "Death of a Salesman," a teacher's wife is assaulted in her new home, which leaves him determined to find the perpetrator over his wife's traumatized objections.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

overview: When a woman dying of cancer in early twentieth-century Sweden is visited by her two sisters, long-repressed feelings between the siblings rise to the surface.

title: Brief Encounter
overview: Meeting a stranger in a railway station, a woman is tempted to cheat on her husband.

title: Gifted
overview: Frank, a single man raising his child prodigy niece Mary, is drawn into a custody battle with his mother.

title: Die Welle
overview: A high school teacher's experiment to demonstrate to his students what life is like under a dictatorship spins horribly out of control when he forms a social unit with a life of its own.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: Rocky
overview: A small-time boxer gets a supremely rare chance to fight a heavy-weight champion in a bout in which he strives to go the distance for his self-respect.

title: Todo sobre mi madre
overview: Young Esteban wants to become a writer and also to discover the identity of his second mother, a trans woman, carefully concealed by his mother Manuela.
